{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775886747646,"sessionID":"ses_284e8dafeffe311zXel70RPgap","part":{"id":"prt_d7b176a7f001k8zpLl15DuNEeM","messageID":"msg_d7b174b2b0010oqFsbY6zwsVai","sessionID":"ses_284e8dafeffe311zXel70RPgap","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:2","state":{"status":"error","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/delta-spec.md","content":"# Delta Specification: CLI Build Command\n\n## AR: AR-021 ŌĆö CLI build ÕæĮõ╗ż\n\n**Module:** cmd/cli  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n**Priority:** P0\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nThe `build` command is responsible for building container images from packaged agent workspaces. It supports both local Docker builds and cloud-based builds, with automatic version increment and metadata management.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: CLI Build Options\n\nThe system SHALL expose a `build` subcommand with configurable options for workspace path, proxy settings, cloud provider selection, and output directory.\n\n#### Scenario: Build with default options\n- **GIVEN** the CLI is installed and importable\n- **WHEN** the user runs `agentcube build` without any options\n- **THEN** the command SHALL use: `workspace` = `\".\"` (`-f` / `--workspace`, `str`, show_default=True); `proxy` = `None` (`-p` / `--proxy`, `Optional[str]`); `cloud_provider` = `None` (`--cloud-provider`, `Optional[str]`); `output` = `None` (`--output`, `Optional[str]`); `verbose` = `False` (`--verbose`, `bool`)\n\n#### Scenario: Build with custom workspace path\n- **GIVEN** a valid agent workspace exists at `/path/to/agent`\n- **WHEN** the user runs `agentcube build -f /path/to/agent`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL resolve the workspace to the provided absolute path and proceed with the build\n\n#### Scenario: Build with proxy configuration\n- **GIVEN** the user needs to use a custom proxy for dependency resolution\n- **WHEN** the user runs `agentcube build -p http://proxy.example.com:8080`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL pass the proxy URL to `BuildRuntime.build()` as `proxy` option\n\n#### Scenario: Build with cloud provider\n- **GIVEN** the metadata `build_mode` is set to `cloud`\n- **WHEN** the user runs `agentcube build --cloud-provider huawei`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL pass the cloud provider name to `BuildRuntime._build_cloud()` for cloud-specific build orchestration\n\n#### Scenario: Build with output directory\n- **GIVEN** the user wants build artifacts in a specific location\n- **WHEN** the user runs `agentcube build --output /custom/output/dir`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL pass the output path to `BuildRuntime.build()` and ensure the directory exists\n\n#### Scenario: Build with verbose logging\n- **GIVEN** the user wants detailed build output\n- **WHEN** the user runs `agentcube build --verbose`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL set verbose mode on `BuildRuntime` and log detailed progress information\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Build Mode Resolution\n\nThe system SHALL determine the build mode from metadata, supporting both local Docker builds and cloud-based builds.\n\n#### Scenario: Local build mode (default)\n- **GIVEN** the `agent_metadata.yaml` contains `build_mode: local` or no build_mode specified\n- **WHEN** `build` command executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL invoke `BuildRuntime._build_local()` to build the Docker image locally\n\n#### Scenario: Cloud build mode\n- **GIVEN** the `agent_metadata.yaml` contains `build_mode: cloud`\n- **WHEN** `build` command executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL invoke `BuildRuntime._build_cloud()` to trigger a cloud-based build\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Local Docker Build Prerequisites\n\nThe system SHALL validate that Docker is available and running before attempting local builds.\n\n#### Scenario: Docker unavailable\n- **GIVEN** `build_mode` resolves to `local`\n- **WHEN** Docker daemon is not running or not accessible\n- **THEN** `BuildRuntime._validate_build_prerequisites()` SHALL raise `RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")` surfaced via CLI error handling with exit code 1\n\n#### Scenario: Docker available\n- **GIVEN** `build_mode` resolves to `local`\n- **WHEN** Docker daemon is running and accessible via `docker.from_env()`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL proceed with the Docker build process\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Version Increment on Build\n\nThe system SHALL automatically increment the agent version before each build and revert on failure.\n\n#### Scenario: Patch version bump for semantic version\n- **GIVEN** the metadata contains `version: \"1.2.3\"`\n- **WHEN** `BuildRuntime._increment_version()` is called during build\n- **THEN** the version SHALL be incremented to `\"1.2.4\"` (patch bump)\n\n#### Scenario: Version increment with missing patch\n- **GIVEN** the metadata contains `version: \"1.2\"`\n- **WHEN** `BuildRuntime._increment_version()` is called\n- **THEN** the version SHALL be incremented by appending `.1` to become `\"1.2.1\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Version increment fallback for non-semver\n- **GIVEN** the metadata contains `version: \"beta-release\"`\n- **WHEN** `BuildRuntime._increment_version()` is called\n- **THEN** the version SHALL be incremented by appending `-1` to become `\"beta-release-1\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Revert version on build failure\n- **GIVEN** a build is in progress and version was incremented\n- **WHEN** the Docker build fails (e.g., Dockerfile not found, build error)\n- **THEN** the system SHALL revert the metadata version to its original value before the exception propagates\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Docker Image Building\n\nThe system SHALL build Docker images using the Docker SDK with proper tagging and build arguments.\n\n#### Scenario: Build image from Dockerfile\n- **GIVEN** a packaged workspace with `Dockerfile` present\n- **WHEN** `DockerService.build_image()` is called with `dockerfile_path`, `context_path`, `image_name`, and `tag`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL build the image, tag it as `{image_name}:{tag}`, and return `{\"image_name\": str, \"image_id\": str, \"image_size\": str, \"build_time\": str}`\n\n#### Scenario: Build with proxy build arguments\n- **GIVEN** a proxy URL is provided via `--proxy`\n- **WHEN** the Docker build executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL pass `build_args` including `HTTP_PROXY`, `HTTPS_PROXY`, and `NO_PROXY` to `DockerService.build_image()`\n\n#### Scenario: Build with image tag from version\n- **GIVEN** the incremented version is `\"1.2.4\"` and agent name is `\"my-agent\"`\n- **WHEN** the Docker build executes\n- **THEN** the image SHALL be tagged as `my-agent:1.2.4`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Cloud Build Integration\n\nThe system SHALL support cloud-based builds through provider-specific implementations.\n\n#### Scenario: Cloud build with provider configuration\n- **GIVEN** `build_mode` is `cloud` and `--cloud-provider huawei` is specified\n- **WHEN** `BuildRuntime._build_cloud()` is invoked\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use the cloud provider SDK to trigger a remote build with the workspace context\n\n#### Scenario: Cloud build returns artifacts\n- **GIVEN** a cloud build completes successfully\n- **WHEN** `_build_cloud()` returns\n- **THEN** the result SHALL include `image_url`, `image_digest`, `build_id`, and `build_time`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Build Metadata Update\n\nThe system SHALL persist build results to the workspace metadata after successful builds.\n\n#### Scenario: Update metadata after successful build\n- **GIVEN** a local build completed successfully with image `my-agent:1.2.4`\n- **WHEN** `BuildRuntime._update_build_metadata()` is called\n- **THEN** the `agent_metadata.yaml` SHALL be updated with `image.name`, `image.tag`, `image.id`, `image.size`, `build.time`, and `build.status = \"success\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Update metadata with tag override\n- **GIVEN** a build result and explicit tag `\"latest\"`\n- **WHEN** `_update_build_metadata()` is called with `tag=\"latest\"`\n- **THEN** the metadata SHALL record the tag as `\"latest\"` regardless of version\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Build Error Handling\n\nThe system SHALL handle build errors gracefully with appropriate error messages and exit codes.\n\n#### Scenario: Build with missing Dockerfile\n- **GIVEN** the workspace has no `Dockerfile` and pack was not run\n- **WHEN** `build` command executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise an error indicating missing Dockerfile and exit with code 1\n\n#### Scenario: Build with invalid workspace\n- **GIVEN** the workspace path does not exist\n- **WHEN** `build` command executes\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message about invalid workspace path\n\n#### Scenario: Build failure with verbose output\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `agentcube build --verbose`\n- **WHEN** a build error occurs\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print `Error building agent: {e}` in red, print a full traceback, and exit with code 1\n\n#### Scenario: Build failure without verbose output\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `agentcube build` without verbose flag\n- **WHEN** a build error occurs\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print `Error building agent: {e}` in red and exit with code 1 without traceback\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Build Command Integration with Pack\n\nThe system SHALL ensure build command works correctly with pre-packaged workspaces.\n\n#### Scenario: Build after successful pack\n- **GIVEN** the user has run `agentcube pack` successfully in the workspace\n- **WHEN** the user runs `agentcube build`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use the generated `Dockerfile` and `agent_metadata.yaml` from the pack operation\n\n#### Scenario: Build requires pack metadata\n- **GIVEN** the workspace has no `agent_metadata.yaml`\n- **WHEN** the user runs `agentcube build`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise an error indicating that `pack` must be run first\n\n---\n\n## Interface Specification\n\n### Command Signature\n\n```python\ndef build(\n    workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n    proxy: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"-p\", \"--proxy\", help=\"Custom proxy URL for dependency resolution\"),\n    cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--cloud-provider\", help=\"Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\"),\n    output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for build artifacts\"),\n    verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n) -> None:\n```\n\n### Runtime Interface\n\n```python\nclass BuildRuntime:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n    def build(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def _increment_version(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata) -> Any: ...\n    def _validate_build_prerequisites(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n    def _build_local(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def _build_cloud(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def _update_build_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, build_result: Dict[str, str], tag: str = \"latest\") -> None: ...\n```\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\nThe build command depends on:\n\n- `BuildRuntime` from `agentcube.runtime.build_runtime`\n- `MetadataService` from `agentcube.services.metadata_service`\n- `DockerService` from `agentcube.services.docker_service` (for local builds)\n- `AgentMetadata` model for version and image tracking\n\n---\n\n## Output Format\n\n### Success Output\n\n```\nBuilding agent [agent_name]...\nVersion: [version] -> [incremented_version]\nBuild mode: [local|cloud]\n\nŌ£ō Build completed successfully!\n\nImage: [image_name]:[tag]\nImage ID: [image_id]\nImage Size: [image_size]\nBuild Time: [build_time]s\n\nMetadata updated: [metadata_path]\n```\n\n### Error Output\n\n```\nBuilding agent [agent_name]...\n\nError building agent: [error_message]\n\n[traceback if verbose]\n```\n\n---\n\n## Exit Codes\n\n| Code | Meaning |\n|------|---------|\n| 0 | Build successful |\n| 1 | Build failed (error message printed) |\n"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/delta-spec.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775886747638,"end":1775886747644}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775886747663,"sessionID":"ses_284e8dafeffe311zXel70RPgap","part":{"id":"prt_d7b1947fe001w1W4FDeZMNsWAe","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7b174b2b0010oqFsbY6zwsVai","sessionID":"ses_284e8dafeffe311zXel70RPgap","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":35943,"input":4,"output":3087,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":2799,"read":30053}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775886750778,"sessionID":"ses_284e8dafeffe311zXel70RPgap","part":{"id":"prt_d7b195437001S6e27GVMY3zhSV","messageID":"msg_d7b194826001dw50jcDReVH8uc","sessionID":"ses_284e8dafeffe311zXel70RPgap","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775886752462,"sessionID":"ses_284e8dafeffe311zXel70RPgap","part":{"id":"prt_d7b195697001rcB5VqPyXmwnM5","messageID":"msg_d7b194826001dw50jcDReVH8uc","sessionID":"ses_284e8dafeffe311zXel70RPgap","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-017 ŌĆö PicoD JWT Middleware\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-017  \n6: **Module:** pkg/picod  \n7: **Language:** Go  \n8: **Size:** S  \n9: \n10: Provide JWT authentication middleware for the PicoD command execution service, enabling secure API access with token-based authentication, authorization checks, and session validation.\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Requirements\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: JWT Token Validation Middleware\n17: \n18: The system SHALL provide HTTP middleware that validates JWT tokens for PicoD API endpoints.\n19: \n20: #### Scenario: Valid token allows request\n21: - **GIVEN** a valid JWT token in the Authorization header\n22: - **WHEN** a request is made to a PicoD execution endpoint\n23: - **THEN** the middleware SHALL validate the token and allow the request to proceed\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: Missing token returns 401\n26: - **GIVEN** a request without an Authorization header\n27: - **WHEN** the request is processed by the middleware\n28: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 401 with error `{\"error\": \"Unauthorized\", \"message\": \"missing authorization header\"}`\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: Invalid token format returns 401\n31: - **GIVEN** a request with an Authorization header not starting with \"Bearer \"\n32: - **WHEN** the request is processed by the middleware\n33: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 401 with error `{\"error\": \"Unauthorized\", \"message\": \"invalid authorization format\"}`\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Expired token returns 401\n36: - **GIVEN** a request with an expired JWT token\n37: - **WHEN** the middleware validates the token\n38: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 401 with error `{\"error\": \"Unauthorized\", \"message\": \"token expired\"}`\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: Malformed token returns 401\n41: - **GIVEN** a request with a malformed JWT token\n42: - **WHEN** the middleware validates the token\n43: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 401 with error `{\"error\": \"Unauthorized\", \"message\": \"token malformed\"}`\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: Invalid signature returns 401\n46: - **GIVEN** a request with a JWT token signed with wrong key\n47: - **WHEN** the middleware validates the token\n48: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 401 with error `{\"error\": \"Unauthorized\", \"message\": \"token signature invalid\"}`\n49: \n50: ---\n51: \n52: ### Requirement: Token Claims Extraction and Context Propagation\n53: \n54: The system SHALL extract JWT claims and store them in the request context for downstream handlers.\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: Claims stored in context\n57: - **GIVEN** a valid JWT token with session_id claim\n58: - **WHEN** the middleware validates the token\n59: - **THEN** the extracted claims SHALL be stored in the request context\n60: \n61: #### Scenario: Session ID extracted from token\n62: - **GIVEN** a valid JWT token with session_id=\"test-session-123\"\n63: - **WHEN** the middleware processes the request\n64: - **THEN** downstream handlers SHALL be able to retrieve session_id from context\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: User ID extracted from token\n67: - **GIVEN** a valid JWT token with user_id=\"user-456\"\n68: - **WHEN** the middleware processes the request\n69: - **THEN** downstream handlers SHALL be able to retrieve user_id from context\n70: \n71: #### Scenario: Sandbox ID extracted from token\n72: - **GIVEN** a valid JWT token with sandbox_id=\"sandbox-789\"\n73: - **WHEN** the middleware processes the request\n74: - **THEN** downstream handlers SHALL be able to retrieve sandbox_id from context\n75: \n76: #### Scenario: Namespace extracted from token\n77: - **GIVEN** a valid JWT token with namespace=\"default\"\n78: - **WHEN** the middleware processes the request\n79: - **THEN** downstream handlers SHALL be able to retrieve namespace from context\n80: \n81: #### Scenario: Multiple claims extracted\n82: - **GIVEN** a valid JWT token with session_id, user_id, sandbox_id, namespace, and runtime_kind claims\n83: - **WHEN** the middleware processes the request\n84: - **THEN** all claims SHALL be available in the context for downstream use\n85: \n86: ---\n87: \n88: ### Requirement: Session ID Validation Middleware\n89: \n90: The system SHALL verify that the session_id claim is present and valid.\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: Missing session_id returns 403\n93: - **GIVEN** a valid JWT token without a session_id claim\n94: - **WHEN** the request is processed\n95: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 403 with error `{\"error\": \"Forbidden\", \"message\": \"session_id claim is required\"}`\n96: \n97: #### Scenario: Empty session_id returns 403\n98: - **GIVEN** a valid JWT token with empty session_id=\"\"\n99: - **WHEN** the request is processed\n100: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 403 with error `{\"error\": \"Forbidden\", \"message\": \"session_id cannot be empty\"}`\n101: \n102: #### Scenario: Session ID matches request parameter\n103: - **GIVEN** a token with session_id=\"abc123\" and request to /execute/abc123\n104: - **WHEN** the middleware validates session access\n105: - **THEN** the request SHALL be allowed to proceed\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: Session ID mismatch returns 403\n108: - **GIVEN** a token with session_id=\"abc123\" and request to /execute/def456\n109: - **WHEN** the middleware validates session access\n110: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 403 with error `{\"error\": \"Forbidden\", \"message\": \"session access denied\"}`\n111: \n112: ---\n113: \n114: ### Requirement: Optional Authentication Support\n115: \n116: The system SHALL support optional authentication for specific endpoints.\n117: \n118: #### Scenario: Optional auth allows anonymous requests\n119: - **GIVEN** an endpoint with optional authentication enabled\n120: - **WHEN** a request without a token is made\n121: - **THEN** the request SHALL be allowed to proceed without claims in context\n122: \n123: #### Scenario: Optional auth extracts claims when present\n124: - **GIVEN** an endpoint with optional authentication enabled\n125: - **WHEN** a request with a valid token is made\n126: - **THEN** the claims SHALL be extracted and stored in context\n127: \n128: #### Scenario: Optional auth ignores invalid tokens\n129: - **GIVEN** an endpoint with optional authentication enabled\n130: - **WHEN** a request with an invalid token is made\n131: - **THEN** the request SHALL proceed without claims (invalid token is treated as no token)\n132: \n133: ---\n134: \n135: ### Requirement: JWT Configuration\n136: \n137: The system SHALL support configurable JWT settings for the PicoD middleware.\n138: \n139: #### Scenario: Configuration from environment variables\n140: - **GIVEN** environment variables `PICOD_JWT_ISSUER`, `PICOD_JWT_ACCESS_EXPIRY`, and `PICOD_JWT_PUBLIC_KEY`\n141: - **WHEN** the middleware configuration is initialized\n142: - **THEN** the configuration SHALL be populated from these environment variables\n143: \n144: #### Scenario: Configuration with public key PEM\n145: - **GIVEN** a valid RSA public key in PEM format in configuration\n146: - **WHEN** the middleware validates tokens\n147: - **THEN** it SHALL use the configured public key to verify signatures\n148: \n149: #### Scenario: Configuration with JWKS endpoint\n150: - **GIVEN** a JWKS (JSON Web Key Set) endpoint URL in configuration\n151: - **WHEN** the middleware needs to validate tokens\n152: - **THEN** it SHALL fetch the public key from the JWKS endpoint\n153: \n154: #### Scenario: Invalid configuration returns error\n155: - **GIVEN** an invalid JWT configuration (e.g., empty issuer)\n156: - **WHEN** the middleware is initialized\n157: - **THEN** it SHALL return a validation error\n158: \n159: #### Scenario: Default configuration values\n160: - **GIVEN** no environment variables set\n161: - **WHEN** the middleware configuration is loaded\n162: - **THEN** it SHALL use sensible defaults (issuer=\"picod\", expiry=5m)\n163: \n164: ---\n165: \n166: ### Requirement: Token Refresh Support\n167: \n168: The system SHALL support token refresh for extended sessions.\n169: \n170: #### Scenario: Refresh token endpoint\n171: - **GIVEN** a valid refresh token\n172: - **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/auth/refresh` with the refresh token\n173: - **THEN** the server SHALL return a new access token and refresh token pair\n174: \n175: #### Scenario: Expired refresh token returns 401\n176: - **GIVEN** an expired refresh token\n177: - **WHEN** a refresh request is made\n178: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 401 with error `{\"error\": \"Unauthorized\", \"message\": \"refresh token expired\"}`\n179: \n180: #### Scenario: Invalid refresh token returns 401\n181: - **GIVEN** an invalid refresh token\n182: - **WHEN** a refresh request is made\n183: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 401 with error `{\"error\": \"Unauthorized\", \"message\": \"invalid refresh token\"}`\n184: \n185: ---\n186: \n187: ### Requirement: Public Key Endpoint\n188: \n189: The system SHALL expose a public key endpoint for token verification by clients.\n190: \n191: #### Scenario: Get public key\n192: - **GIVEN** the JWT middleware is configured with RSA keys\n193: - **WHEN** a GET request is made to `/.well-known/jwks.json`\n194: - **THEN** the server SHALL return the public key in JWKS format\n195: \n196: #### Scenario: Public key includes key ID\n197: - **GIVEN** the JWT middleware is configured with key versioning\n198: - **WHEN** the JWKS endpoint is queried\n199: - **THEN** the response SHALL include the key ID (kid) for each key\n200: \n201: #### Scenario: Public key algorithm specified\n202: - **GIVEN** the JWKS endpoint is queried\n203: - **WHEN** the response is returned\n204: - **THEN** it SHALL include the algorithm (alg: RS256) and key type (kty: RSA)\n205: \n206: ---\n207: \n208: ### Requirement: Metrics and Observability\n209: \n210: The system SHALL expose metrics for JWT middleware operations.\n211: \n212: #### Scenario: Token validation counter\n213: - **GIVEN** the middleware is processing requests\n214: - **WHEN** metrics endpoint `/metrics` is scraped\n215: - **THEN** it SHALL expose `picod_jwt_validations_total` counter with labels for result (success/failure)\n216: \n217: #### Scenario: Token validation latency\n218: - **GIVEN** the middleware is processing requests\n219: - **WHEN** metrics endpoint `/metrics` is scraped\n220: - **THEN** it SHALL expose `picod_jwt_validation_duration_seconds` histogram\n221: \n222: #### Scenario: Active session tracking\n223: - **GIVEN** tokens are being validated\n224: - **WHEN** metrics endpoint `/metrics` is scraped\n225: - **THEN** it SHALL expose `picod_active_sessions` gauge with session_id labels\n226: \n227: ---\n228: \n229: ### Requirement: Logging\n230: \n231: The system SHALL implement structured logging for JWT middleware operations.\n232: \n233: #### Scenario: Successful authentication logged\n234: - **GIVEN** a request with valid token is processed\n235: - **WHEN** authentication succeeds\n236: - **THEN** a log entry SHALL be written with fields: session_id, user_id, endpoint, duration\n237: \n238: #### Scenario: Failed authentication logged\n239: - **GIVEN** a request with invalid token is processed\n240: - **WHEN** authentication fails\n241: - **THEN** a log entry SHALL be written with fields: error, error_code, endpoint, remote_addr\n242: \n243: #### Scenario: Token refresh logged\n244: - **GIVEN** a token refresh request is processed\n245: - **WHEN** refresh succeeds or fails\n246: - **THEN** a log entry SHALL be written with fields: session_id, result, duration\n247: \n248: ---\n249: \n250: ### Requirement: Error Handling\n251: \n252: The system SHALL provide consistent error responses for authentication failures.\n253: \n254: #### Scenario: WWW-Authenticate header on 401\n255: - **GIVEN** an unauthenticated request\n256: - **WHEN** the middleware returns HTTP 401\n257: - **THEN** the response SHALL include `WWW-Authenticate: Bearer` header\n258: \n259: #### Scenario: JSON error response format\n260: - **GIVEN** an authentication error occurs\n261: - **WHEN** the error response is sent\n262: - **THEN** it SHALL be JSON with fields: error, message, code (optional)\n263: \n264: #### Scenario: Error code classification\n265: - **GIVEN** various authentication failures\n266: - **WHEN** errors are returned\n267: - **THEN** each SHALL have a machine-readable code: TOKEN_EXPIRED, TOKEN_INVALID, TOKEN_MALFORMED, MISSING_CLAIMS\n268: \n269: ---\n270: \n271: ## File Index\n272: \n273: | Path | Purpose |\n274: |------|---------|\n275: | `pkg/picod/jwt_middleware.go` | JWT authentication middleware implementation |\n276: | `pkg/picod/jwt_config.go` | JWT configuration structures and loading |\n277: | `pkg/picod/jwt_types.go` | JWT types and context keys for PicoD |\n278: | `pkg/picod/jwt_handlers.go` | HTTP handlers for auth endpoints (refresh, JWKS) |\n279: | `pkg/picod/errors.go` | JWT and authentication error definitions |\n280: \n281: ---\n282: \n283: ## Dependencies\n284: \n285: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n286: |------------|---------|---------|\n287: | `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | Latest | JWT token parsing and validation |\n288: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/router` | Local | Shared JWT types and utilities |\n289: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Latest | Structured logging |\n290: | `github.com/prometheus/client_golang` | Latest | Metrics collection |\n291: \n292: ---\n293: \n294: ## API Endpoints\n295: \n296: | Method | Path | Auth Required | Description |\n297: |--------|------|---------------|-------------|\n298: | POST | `/execute/{session_id}` | Yes | Execute command in sandbox |\n299: | GET | `/execute/{id}/status` | Yes | Get execution status |\n300: | GET | `/execute/{id}/output` | Yes | Stream execution output |\n301: | DELETE | `/execute/{id}` | Yes | Cancel execution |\n302: | POST | `/auth/refresh` | No | Refresh access token |\n303: | GET | `/.well-known/jwks.json` | No | Get public keys in JWKS format |\n304: \n305: ---\n306: \n307: ## Integration Points\n308: \n309: | Component | Integration |\n310: |-----------|-------------|\n311: | `pkg/router` | Reuses JWTManager for token validation; imports TokenClaims type |\n312: | `pkg/picod/executor.go` | Reads session_id from context to validate execution requests |\n313: | `pkg/store` | May store refresh token metadata for revocation |\n314: | `pkg/workloadmanager` | Coordinates JWT configuration across components |\n315: \n316: ---\n317: \n318: ## Notes\n319: \n320: - The PicoD JWT middleware leverages the existing `pkg/router` JWT implementation where possible\n321: - Token claims must include `session_id` for all PicoD execution endpoints\n322: - The middleware supports both mandatory and optional authentication patterns\n323: - Public keys are exposed via JWKS endpoint for external verification\n324: - Metrics are prefixed with `picod_` to distinguish from router metrics\n\n(End of file - total 324 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-017 ŌĆö PicoD JWT Middleware\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-017  \n**Module:** pkg/picod  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S  \n\nProvide JWT authentication middleware for the PicoD command execution service, enabling secure API access with token-based authentication, authorization checks, and session validation.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: JWT Token Validation Middleware\n\nThe system SHALL provide HTTP middleware that validates JWT tokens for PicoD API endpoints.\n\n#### Scenario: Valid token allows request","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775886752451,"end":1775886752459}}}}
