{"type":"text","timestamp":1775887046439,"sessionID":"ses_284e8dafeffe311zXel70RPgap","part":{"id":"prt_d7b1d6c23001x5EfOZgF4ZvrGG","messageID":"msg_d7b1d105e0012sm3Purahj7p3r","sessionID":"ses_284e8dafeffe311zXel70RPgap","type":"text","text":"I've successfully created the delta specification for the CLI build command. The file `delta-spec-cli-build.md` includes:\n\n## Summary\n\n**AR-021 ŌĆö CLI Build Command** specification with:\n\n### Requirements (9 total)\n1. **CLI Build Options** - 6 scenarios covering default options, workspace path, proxy, cloud provider, output directory, and verbose logging\n2. **Build Mode Resolution** - 2 scenarios for local vs cloud build modes\n3. **Local Docker Build Prerequisites** - 2 scenarios for Docker availability validation\n4. **Version Increment on Build** - 4 scenarios for semver bumping and failure revert\n5. **Docker Image Building** - 3 scenarios for image building, proxy args, and tagging\n6. **Cloud Build Integration** - 2 scenarios for cloud provider builds\n7. **Build Metadata Update** - 2 scenarios for metadata persistence\n8. **Build Error Handling** - 4 scenarios for various error conditions\n9. **Build Command Integration with Pack** - 2 scenarios for pack dependency\n\n### Additional Sections\n- **Interface Specification** - Command signature and `BuildRuntime` class interface\n- **File Index** - Relevant source files\n- **Dependencies** - Required Python packages\n- **Output Format** - Success and error output examples\n- **Exit Codes** - Exit code meanings\n- **Integration Points** - Component relationships\n\nAll scenarios follow the **GIVEN/WHEN/THEN** format as specified.","time":{"start":1775887046435,"end":1775887046435}}}
